<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Thu, 14 May 2026 13:27:02 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>人类与机器意识 |帝国理工队的穆雷·沙纳汉</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/human-vs-machine-consciousness-imperials-murray-shanahan</link><description>&lt;img src="https://politepol.com/fd/NjxHZtldG2if.xml" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 14 May 2026 13:26:59 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/human-vs-machine-consciousness-imperials-murray-shanahan</guid></item><item><title>大脑组胺图将基因与大脑功能和心理健康联系起来</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/brain-histamine-map-connects-genes-to-brain-function-and-mental-health</link><description>伦敦国王学院和波尔图大学的新研究绘制了大脑中的组胺系统。组胺是一种更常与过敏相关的分子，它在大脑功能中发挥着独立但人们知之甚少的作用。这项研究解决了这一差距，构建了第一个组胺系统的多尺度图，涵盖从遗传学到行为和相关心理健康状况的范围。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/brain-histamine-map-connects-genes-to-brain-function-and-mental-health3.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 14 May 2026 13:11:59 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/brain-histamine-map-connects-genes-to-brain-function-and-mental-health</guid></item><item><title>自我与信仰之间：宗教参与自恋的动机、情感和认知维度</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/between-ego-and-faith-motivational-affective-and-cognitive-dimensions-of-religious-engagement-in-narcissism</link><description>乍一看，自恋和宗教似乎不太可能是一对。宗教传统通常提倡谦逊、无私和社区关怀。自恋是一种以自我中心、优越感和强烈的权利感为特征的人格特征。这种鲜明的对比提出了一个有趣的问题：具有强烈自恋特征的人如何与宗教信仰和社区互动。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/between-ego-and-faith-motivational-affective-and-cognitive-dimensions-of-religious-engagement-in-narcissism.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 14 May 2026 12:56:59 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/between-ego-and-faith-motivational-affective-and-cognitive-dimensions-of-religious-engagement-in-narcissism</guid></item><item><title>在冰中寻找星尘</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/finding-stardust-in-the-ice</link><description>在过去的数万年里，我们的太阳系一直在穿越当地的星际云 (LIC)，这是太阳附近的 15 个气体和尘埃云之一。地球表面发现了可能来自 LIC 的尘埃，超新星产生的铁同位素表明其星际起源（参见&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/finding-stardust-in-the-ice.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 14 May 2026 12:41:59 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/finding-stardust-in-the-ice</guid></item><item><title>中微子质量的固态途径</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/a-solid-state-pathway-to-neutrino-mass</link><description>新的密度泛函理论计算描述了与石墨烯结合的氚的放射性衰变，提供了一种模拟实验的方法，可以打开更清晰的中微子质量窗口。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/a-solid-state-pathway-to-neutrino-mass.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 14 May 2026 12:26:59 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/a-solid-state-pathway-to-neutrino-mass</guid></item><item><title>具有内部隐形功能的隐形斗篷</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/an-invisibility-cloak-with-internal-invisibility</link><description>新的超材料设计消除了可能对隐形和传感应用产生不利影响的内部扭曲。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/an-invisibility-cloak-with-internal-invisibility2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 14 May 2026 12:11:59 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/an-invisibility-cloak-with-internal-invisibility</guid></item><item><title>杠铃“鞭子”对奥运举重的影响可能比举重运动员意识到的还要大</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/barbell-whip-may-shape-olympic-lifts-more-than-lifters-realize</link><description>在奥运会举重比赛中，一公斤的杠铃片就可以决定金牌和银牌的区别。精英运动员必须尽可能地利用一切手段来发挥自己的优势。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/barbell-whip-may-shape-olympic-lifts-more-than-lifters-realize.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 14 May 2026 11:56:59 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/barbell-whip-may-shape-olympic-lifts-more-than-lifters-realize</guid></item><item><title>液晶可以在室温下按需形成斯格明子</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/liquid-crystals-enable-on-demand-skyrmion-formation-at-room-temperature</link><description>研究人员最近发现了一种利用光、热和电场来召唤磁性材料中有用结构的新方法。一项新研究描述了这种新方法&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/liquid-crystals-enable-on-demand-skyrmion-formation-at-room-temperature2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 14 May 2026 11:41:59 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/liquid-crystals-enable-on-demand-skyrmion-formation-at-room-temperature</guid></item><item><title>大部分为空的泡沫推翻了电子束停止的假设</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/mostly-empty-foam-overturns-assumptions-of-electron-beam-stopping</link><description>当物理学家向材料发射快速电子束时，他们通常需要确切地知道这些电子在穿过材料时会损失多少能量。通过发表在&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/mostly-empty-foam-overturns-assumptions-of-electron-beam-stopping2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 14 May 2026 11:26:59 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/mostly-empty-foam-overturns-assumptions-of-electron-beam-stopping</guid></item><item><title>两种过渡金属二硫属化物中的原子带暗示了长期理论化的量子态</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/atomic-bands-in-two-transition-metal-dichalcogenides-hint-at-long-theorized-quantum-state</link><description>绝缘体是电子不能自由移动的材料。过去的理论研究预测存在一种被称为阻塞原子绝缘体（OAI）的不寻常绝缘状态，其中电子位于晶体内部，而它们的电荷中心位于原子之间的空白空间中，而不是原子本身。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/atomic-bands-in-two-transition-metal-dichalcogenides-hint-at-long-theorized-quantum-state.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 14 May 2026 11:11:59 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/atomic-bands-in-two-transition-metal-dichalcogenides-hint-at-long-theorized-quantum-state</guid></item></channel></rss>